{
  "stem": "14168.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You couldn't have entered into a valid contract, and we can't admit you to Great Britain.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she just talked-- must have talked as fast as I did to the Gestapo, to convince the British passport control to let her land in Southampton.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She went to the Bloomsbury House, it was called at the time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That is the Jewish Relief Committee.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they arranged for a job with a Belgian family, a family whose-- the husband worked for Reuters, for the British agency.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she stayed there, in London about four months until I arranged for marriage by proxy, but that is another story.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was off to Peru.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had a problem, landing in Peru.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't-- can't go into detail on this, but the Peruvian government got wind, through a passenger of my boat, who-- that the visas on which we were sailing for Peru had been obtained in Paris.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that Paris visas for German residents should-- should be invalidated, because the competent Peruvian authority was the consul general in Berlin, who I understood was a great anti-Semite and wouldn't have given us any visa.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He came on board-- the Peruvian consul in Antwerp came on board our ship and told the captain not to permit us to sail any further, and the-- because our visas were invalid.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The captain told him to get the hell off the boat, because he was carrying passengers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "According to his instructions, they had paid both ways.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But Peru was warned, and we had tremendous difficulties, landing in Peru.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I first landed in Baltimore, where I met a-- I-- I gave an interview to the I was the only English-speaking person on board that vessel.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then New York, and we understood-- we tried to do our best.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
